---
/**
 * /legal — Legal hub.
 *
 * Index page linking to the three primary legal documents. The hub
 * stayed at /legal so existing inbound links (footer, login page,
 * external references) continue to resolve. The detailed pages now
 * live under /legal/<doc>.
 */
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="Legal &amp; privacy · Tournamental"
  description="Terms of Service, Privacy Policy, and Cookie Notice for the Tournamental open-source tournament prediction platform."
  ogImage="/og/legal.png"
>
  <article class="container-prose pt-16 pb-16 prose-vt">
    <p class="text-ink-500 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-2">
      Legal &amp; privacy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-ink-500 text-sm mt-3">Last updated: 13 May 2026.</p>

    <p class="mt-6">
      Tournamental is a subsidiary of <strong>Growth Spurt Ltd</strong>,
      a New Zealand company headquartered in Auckland. The Platform
      code is open source under Apache 2.0; the docs are CC-BY 4.0;
      the brand and affiliate codes are owned by Growth Spurt Ltd.
    </p>

    <h2>The documents</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a class="link" href="/legal/terms"><strong>Terms of Service</strong></a>
        — what you agree to when you use the Platform. Covers
        accounts, acceptable use, user content, the open-source
        licence, the Drips Network contributor revenue share, the
        no-gambling position for the free tier, the disclaimer of
        warranties, the liability cap, and the governing law.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="link" href="/legal/privacy"><strong>Privacy Policy</strong></a>
        — what we collect, why, how long we keep it, who we share it
        with, and what choices you have. Covers NZ Privacy Act 2020,
        GDPR, UK GDPR, CCPA, and the Australian Privacy Act.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="link" href="/legal/cookies"><strong>Cookie Notice</strong></a>
        — every cookie and storage key we use, in a table; plus a
        preference centre you can change at any time.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Real-money play</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>The free-tier Tournamental game has no entry fee and no
      cash prize.</strong> The Platform tracks predictions, scores,
      and rankings only. Where syndicate hosts run a real-money pool
      among their members, those funds are held and disbursed by the
      host directly between participants. Tournamental is not a party
      to the transaction and does not handle, hold, or disburse
      those funds.
    </p>
    <p>
      A future on-chain prize-pool feature (see
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/21-onchain-sweepstakes-oracle.md">doc 21</a>)
      is gated on a passing external smart-contract audit and on
      compliance with the licensing regime of each jurisdiction we
      operate in. We will not enable on-chain prize-pool participation
      for users in jurisdictions where it would be regulated as
      gambling.
    </p>

    <h2>Security and disclosures</h2>
    <p>
      Responsible disclosures:
      <a class="link" href="mailto:security@tournamental.com">security@tournamental.com</a>.
      We commit to acknowledging within 48 hours and patching within 14
      days for high-severity issues. See
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/SECURITY.md">SECURITY.md</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Licences</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Code: <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/LICENSE">Apache 2.0</a>.</li>
      <li>Docs: <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/LICENSE-DOCS">CC-BY 4.0</a>.</li>
      <li>Player photographs: Wikimedia Commons under their respective
        CC-BY-SA terms; full attribution at
        <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/apps/web/public/CREDITS.md">CREDITS.md</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      All enquiries:
      <a class="link" href="mailto:info@tournamental.com">info@tournamental.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
